{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c054885b-ade5-4cf8-88cd-c64a05c27a78","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. Update packages\n- **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n- **Upgrade** `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n- Keep your `nunit` package as-is\n\n### 2. Enable the new platform\nAdd this to your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Run tests\nTests now run via:\n```bash\ndotnet test          # still works (delegates to new platform)\ndotnet run           # also works — project becomes executable\n```\n\n### Key notes\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **v5+** acts as both the adapter and the platform host — no extra package needed.\n- `.runsettings` files are still supported but some VSTest-specific settings may need adjustment.\n- If you use `dotnet test` filters, the syntax stays the same (`--filter`).\n- Extensions (loggers, coverage, etc.) may need their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad4162b2-a04d-4dac-8aec-bde3486e0bb7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":366,"requestId":"A02C:2D289A:C0597E:E0328E:69FE84F7"},"id":"cb41c6a3-d1cc-456c-b2c6-7a4f9a82399f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:12.998Z","parentId":"a671a5ba-3b13-4115-9e9d-09968de7bb88"}
